>I'm listing the books that seem to work for my regular reading 4th graders
>(vs those who read up) and some that they have already passed by and would
>probably be great for 3rd graders.  Monica
>
>
>I second Uma Krishnaswamy's THE GRAND PLAN TO FIX EVERYTHING
> Atinuke's ANNA HIBISCUS books
>Lauren Child's CLARICE BEAN novels
>Sheila Turnage's THREE TIMES LUCKY
>Rebecca Stead's WHEN YOU REACH ME
>Sonya Hartnett's SADIE AND RATZ
>Christopher Paul Curtis's THE MIGHTY MISS MALONE
>Katherine Applegate's THE ONE AND ONLY IVAN
>Diana Wynne Jones' EARWIG AND THE WITCH
>Tom Angleberger's FAKE MUSTACHE
>Brian Selznick's INVENTION OF HUGO CABRET and WONDERSTRUCK
>Jennifer Holm's TURTLE IN PARADISE
>Barry Deutch's HEREVILLE: HOW MIRKA GOT HER SWORD (there's a sequel just
>out, but I haven't seen it yet)
